    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-03T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-03T12:00:00-05:00" n="118"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.CC/4–2435: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-03T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 3, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 3—2:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3382. ReDeptel 2051, March 16, midnight.<note n="89" xml:id="d118fn1">Not
                        printed, but see footnote 60, <ref target="#pg_126">p. 126</ref>.</note> The
                    attention of the Foreign Office was invited to the three points suggested by the
                    Chinese for inclusion in the charter of the International Organization and a
                    reply has now been received from the Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs
                    noting that the US Government perceives no objection to meeting the wish of
                    Chinese Government and stating that the British Government for its part also
                    sees no objection thereto and is prepared to support the Chinese proposal at the
                    San Francisco Conference.<note n="90" xml:id="d118fn2">For the Soviet attitude,
                        see minutes of meeting of the “Big Four” Foreign Ministers, April 23, <ref
                            target="#pg_363">p. 363</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
